<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' CHOICE: EVA LUNA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Elena Brunet 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
by Isabel Allende; translated from the Spanish by Margaret Sayers Peden (Alfred 
A. Knopf: $18.95; 272 pp.) 
</P>
<P>
" 'Eva Luna' is a picaresque tale of a South American child who likes to tell 
stories and grows up to write novels. An inventive political fable from one of 
South America's most interesting writers." Elena Brunet 
</P>
</TEXT>
