111 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANIMALS AS ACTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I wish Hearne hadn't given the impression, even unintentionally, to people who 
will never in any other way hear of him, that Descartes campaigned for 
vivisection ("He held that animals are unconscious mechanisms that only appear 
to feel and think. . . . On that view, even nailing a dog to a board and 
cutting his chest open without anesthesia is not cruel. . . ."). But thank you 
for the article. If I'm lucky enough to have another dog I'll go about what's 
between him and me more intelligently. I do have a old horse I treat kindly. 
I'll tell her what you said, about how she ought to be given her chance to be 
proud -- still. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT H. WORMHOUDT 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 
</P>
</TEXT>
