<HEADLINE>
<P>
POPEYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK GOLDSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EBB TIDE: Is Power 106 morning deejay Jay Thomas over the hill? Or maybe 
running scared? We're starting to wonder -- especially after he made such a big 
deal about soliciting names for his morning show -- and then picked "The Power 
106 Morning Zoo," an embarrassingly lame name already in use at dozens of 
stations around the country. Is it possible Thomas chose "Morning Zoo" because 
it was the same moniker his new rival -- arriving KIQQ-FM deejay Scott Shannon 
-- used for his morning program at New York's top-rated Z100 station? 
</P>
</TEXT>
