<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE COLOR OF WAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re director Oliver Stone's glorifying of white males in the Vietnam War ("New 
Film Brings the Old War Home," Jan. 22): Many thousands of Vietnam casualties 
were African Americans -- heroic, dedicated and patriotic soldiers. Stone has 
portrayed African American military men as lazy, inferior and cowardly. The 
world knows better. 
</P>
<P>
Please! Please! Spare us from another "White Platoon"! 
</P>
<P>
JOHN JOHNSON 
</P>
<P>
Venice Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
