<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIXING IT UP WITH PETER SELLARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After reading Peter Sellars' commentary in "The Big Mix" Feb. 5, I nearly fell 
into a suicidal despondency because I'm culturally anemic, American and white. 
</P>
<P>
But before I reached for a razor blade, I began reviewing my recent cultural 
experiences to see how many could be categorized as ethnically themed. I tried 
to visualize how many involved a different skin color, hoping desperately that 
Thai food would count. 
</P>
<P>
Is this what Sellars wants? With his separatist attitude, he is defeating his 
own purpose, building partitions instead of breaking them. To pinpoint any art 
as black, Asian, Hispanic, etc., is a disservice to the artists, who probably 
like me would have never given it a thought and have taken for granted that it 
was simply American art. 
</P>
<P>
BOBBIE DEARING 
</P>
<P>
West Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
