<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHN TOWER'S NOMINATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Based on personal experience, I have an offbeat reason for supporting the 
confirmation of Tower even though he has been very thick with the defense 
establishment for many years. 
</P>
<P>
During the Korean War, while serving as personnel officer of a Naval station, I 
had the additional duty of being in charge of the brig. Every one of my guards 
had a long disciplinary record. The place ran perfectly because no one could 
put anything over on those guys. 
</P>
<P>
I am not impugning Tower in any way. I am just saying that a fox can guard a 
chicken coop. 
</P>
<P>
FLOYD A. OLIVER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
