<HEADLINE>
<P>
WATER PROBLEM: 'THE DRY YEARS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After reading your editorial I was struck by the gross inequity that would be 
imposed by an across the board, mandatory 10% reduction in water usage. Last 
summer, my husband and I, along with many of our friends and neighbors, cut our 
water usage by 10%. To subsequently impose another 10% reduction on us and 
others who voluntarily complied with the program would be, not only unfair, but 
a hardship. I feel that the Department of Water and Power should either use the 
usage figures from 1987 as the base value, or should look at setting a standard 
for usage based on the size of the household and property. 
</P>
<P>
SUSAN GROSSMAN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
