<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE BARGAIN CORNER: HOTEL DISCOUNT PLANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK ADLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Several hotel discount programs are in effect. 
</P>
<P>
Days Inns plans to continue its Simple Super Saver program indefinitely at more 
than 720 properties in 47 states plus Canada. 
</P>
<P>
The cost is $19 to $39 a night, up to four guests per room, at participating 
hotels. Prices represent up to 20% in savings over regular rates. In some 
cities there might be a $10 surcharge. 
</P>
<P>
Reservations must be made at least 29 days in advance and the first night must 
be prepaid. No weekend or holiday restrictions, but rooms are on a 
space-available basis. No penalty for cancellations up to 15 days before 
arrival. 
</P>
<P>
Contact Days Inns toll-free at (800) 325-2525 or travel agents. 
</P>
<P>
Outrigger Hotels Hawaii has expanded and extended its "Waikiki Free Ride" 
car/room promotion, which provides a free car rental for each day in the hotel 
at regular room rates. Car-rental taxes, however, are not included. Cars are 
compacts with automatic shifts, from Dollar Rent A Car. 
</P>
<P>
Request the package when you make a reservation. Contact Outrigger Hotels at 
(800) 367-5170 or travel agents. 
</P>
<P>
Check the Baja Travel Pass discount booklet offered by the Hoteles La Pinta 
chain. The $199 booklet provides four coupons that represent about a 25% 
discount off regular rates. Coupons are for two and include breakfasts at the 
hotel. A 15% room tax is extra. 
</P>
<P>
Participating La Pinta hotels are in Ensenada, San Quintin, Catalina, Guerro 
Negro, San Ignacio and Loreto. Regular rate at La Pinta hotels, except at 
Ensenada and Loreto, is $58 per room for one or two guests. With the coupon it 
would drop to about $50. 
</P>
<P>
La Pinta hotel in Ensenada has a weekend rate of $60 and weekday rate of $45. 
At Loreto it's $49 all week. 
</P>
<P>
Coupons are valid through this year. Contact the hotel's representative, San 
Diego-based Amex Ltd., at (800) 262-2656. JACK ADLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
