<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFFICE, HANGAR WORK TO START 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phillips Financial Group, an Agoura Hills-based development and financial 
concern, will begin work next month on a $5.7-million office and hangar complex 
at Oxnard Airport. 
</P>
<P>
The project, at 1701 W. 5th St., will have 64,000 square feet of office space. 
Plans also call for construction of 15,000 square feet of new hangar area and 
the remodeling of 26,000 square feet of existing hangar space. 
</P>
<P>
Aero-Flite Inc., a diversified aviation firm, will be the project's anchor 
tenant. Construction is expected to be completed by the end of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
