<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONSTRUCTION STARTS ON POSTAL CENTER IN INDUSTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Major Processing Complex to Be Finished in Early 1990, Will Serve San Gabriel, 
Pomona, Walnut Valleys 
</P>
<P>
Construction has begun on a $61.5-million postal facility in City of Industry 
to serve a 375-square-mile area encompassing Alhambra and sections of the San 
Gabriel, Walnut and Pomona valleys. 
</P>
<P>
The facility, at 15421 E. Gale Ave., will be the Alhambra Management Sectional 
Center of the U.S. Postal Service, encompassing 502,000 square feet of space as 
a full-service post office and mail processing center. Completion is expected 
in the spring of 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Observation galleries of 4,000 linear feet in the main mail processing area 
will enable postal inspectors to observe the work below. The loading dock will 
contain 41 locations. 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena-based Jacobs Engineering Group is providing the architecture and 
engineering services. George Hyman Construction Co. of Bethesda, Md., is the 
contractor. 
</P>
