CALIFORNIAN TO HEAD COUNCIL FOR HOUSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Karney Hodge, director of the California Housing Finance Agency, has been 
elected president of the National Council of State Housing Agencies. 
</P>
<P>
NCSHA is a national trade association comprised of state housing finance 
agencies that issue revenue bonds to underwrite single-family and multifamily 
housing for low- and moderate-income households. 
</P>
<P>
"Of paramount priority for the future success of home ownership programs is the 
extension of the federal mortgage revenue bond authority," Hodge said, "and we 
will continue to support legislation that extends this valuable financing 
tool." Under his direction, the California Housing Finance Agency was one of 
the first agencies to receive Standard &amp; Poor's "Top-Tier" designation. 
</P>
