<TEXT>
<P>
British Airways on Saturday gave its fleet of supersonic Concorde jets a clean 
bill of health after safety checks following the discovery of small cracks in 
the roof structure of one plane. 
</P>
<P>
The airline made what it called precautionary checks on five Concordes that had 
made more than 3,500 landings. 
</P>
<P>
