<HEADLINE>
<P>
POPE WILL MAKE HIS FIFTH VISIT TO AFRICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VATICAN CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pope John Paul II will visit Madagascar, Zambia, Malawi and the French Indian 
Ocean island of Reunion from April 28 to May 6, the Vatican announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
It will be the pontiff's fifth trip to Africa and his 41st outside Italy since 
he was elected in 1978. 
</P>
</TEXT>
