<P>
FIREBALL IN GETAWAY CAR SUBDUES WOULD-BE ROBBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A would-be robber who was doused with gasoline in an attempt to hold up a 
filling station was engulfed in a fireball that erupted in the getaway car, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified man suffered burns over 80% of his body and was in critical 
condition at a hospital, a police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver of the getaway car, his clothing also in flames, was seen running 
from the explosion Friday night, the spokesman said. 
</P>
