<P>
BANNING GAY SPEAKERS AT CORONA DEL MAR HIGH SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corona del Mar senior Doug Shulein's petition to overturn Supt. John Nicoll's 
prohibition of homosexual speakers in a supervised high school classroom 
psychology class comes as a breath of fresh air to a stagnant atmosphere that 
has developed over the past few weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Shulein (and other responsible, well-informed students and parents alike) have 
learned more about the workings of a free democratic society than some of our 
less-enlightened colleagues. This latter well-intentioned group would continue 
to protect us all from social and political evils -- the 
"we-know-what's-best-for-you" approach that is all too common amongst fearful 
persons. 
</P>
<P>
Obviously, I agree with Doug Shulein. The best method of dealing with a complex 
issue -- be it homosexuality, drugs, firearms or other social dilemmas that 
permeate our society -- is through trying to understand all component parts. 
Our generation has not done well. Our children should be allowed the 
opportunity to do better. 
</P>
<P>
ELLIOTT C. MERCER 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar 
</P>
