<TEXT>
<P>
The yacht Thursday's Child, zigzagging north against strong head winds, is 
expected to arrive in San Francisco Bay today to beat by eight days the New 
York-San Francisco speed record of 89 days 8 hours, set by the clipper ship 
Flying Cloud 135 years ago. 
</P>
<P>
Since Nov. 23, Thursday's Child, a 10-ton, stripped-down racing machine, has 
logged some 15,000 miles in a voyage around dreaded Cape Horn. The period 
included a stop at the Falkland Islands to make repairs from a collision with 
an unknown object. 
</P>
