<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SMILEY, STERBENS LEAD MOORPARK WOMEN TO 2ND CONSECUTIVE WSC TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Behind Susie Smiley's 12 points and Kristie Sterbens' 11 points, the Moorpark 
College women's basketball team defeated visiting Santa Barbara, 59-51, 
Saturday to clinch its second consecutive Western State Conference Northern 
Division title. 
</P>
<P>
Kerrie Marshall came off the bench to score 10 points and grab 10 rebounds for 
Moorpark (20-7, 8-3 in conference play). The Lady Raiders have won 20 or more 
games in each of the past three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
In other women's games: 
</P>
<P>
Valley 74, Santa Monica 68 -- The Lady Monarchs converted a season-high 65% of 
their field-goal attempts to win their eighth WSC game in a row at Santa 
Monica. 
</P>
<P>
Sandrine Rocher came off the bench to lead Valley (24-3, 9-1) with 16 points. 
Ruth Aguilar and Tisa Rush each added 15. 
</P>
<P>
CS Northridge 74, Cal Poly SLO 47 -- Julie Arlotto had 15 points and 12 
rebounds for the Lady Matadors in a California Collegiate Athletic Assn. game 
at CSUN. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge (17-6, 5-3) made 47.6% of its field-goal attempts. Bridgette Ealy 
scored 14 points and had seven rebounds and Paula Lucas added 10 points for the 
Lady Matadors. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons 71, Glendale 59 -- Tressie Millender had 28 points and 15 rebounds for 
Canyons in a WSC game at Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons went on a 6-0 run to take a 36-21 lead early in the second half. 
Glendale staged a brief rally late in the game, trimming Canyons' lead to 
51-43, but Millender and Debbie Bernard, who combined for 42 points, helped the 
Lady Cougars regain control. 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific 69, Cal Lutheran 63 -- Heidi Griffith scored 26 points and Dani 
Elton added 18 points for the Regals (6-14, 3-5) in the Golden State Athletic 
Conference game at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 82, Canyons 75 -- The Vaqueros continued their mastery over Canyons in 
the WSC game at Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
Perfection was not, however, what Glendale Coach Brian Beauchemin saw in the 
first half as the Vaqueros (16-10, 7-5) squandered a 20-11 lead and fell into a 
38-38 halftime tie. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons guard Larry Allbritton made a three-point basket to give Canyons its 
first lead at 36-35 in the closing minutes of the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Clark scored a game-high 21 points for Canyons (13-16, 4-8). 
</P>
<P>
 -- DAVID SALKIN 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 86, Azusa Pacific 82 -- The Kingsmen outscored Azusa Pacific, 6-2, 
in the last two minutes to clinch the GSAC victory at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Demeter led Cal Lutheran (9-15, 2-7) with 21 points and Steve deLaveaga 
added 19. Trailing, 45-42, at halftime, Cal Lutheran outscored Azusa Pacific, 
44-37, in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
The Master's 105, Southwestern (Phoenix, Ariz.) 63 -- Six players scored in 
double figures for the Mustangs in a nonconference game at The Master's. 
</P>
<P>
David Moore (15 points), Jason Webster (14), Gerald Thomas (12), Phil Hahn 
(12), Stuart Epperson (10) and Rocky Shipes (10) led the way as Master's 
(13-12) rolled to a 57-24 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara 81, Moorpark 57 -- The Raiders fell to 16-12, 6-6 in the Western 
State Conference despite a school-record 27 rebounds by Greg Taylor. Taylor's 
total surpassed Rick Dyess' 26, set against L. A. Trade Tech in the 1968-69 
season. 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos 5, Canyons 1 -- Tom Diaz limited the Cougars to three hits in a 
nonconference game at Cerritos. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons (2-2) scored its only run in the seventh when Donnie Pedersen led off 
with a triple and scored on Ernie Perez's single. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura 7, Mission 0 -- Brent Cookson's two-run triple in the fifth inning led 
the Pirates in a nonconference game at Mission. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Garcia (0-1), who allowed only one hit -- but four runs -- in five innings 
took the loss. 
</P>
<P>
Valley 3, Kings River 1 -- Tim DeGrasse allowed four hits in 8 1/3 innings and 
Steve Slattery worked out of a bases-loaded, one-out jam in the ninth inning 
for the Monarchs in the Kings River tournament. Greg Struhl doubled and tripled 
and Ray Sabado tripled for Valley (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 13, Victor Valley 4 -- Kris Kaelin hit two home runs and Darin Furlong 
went 4 for 5 with a two-run triple in the nonconference game at Victor Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Willie Leighton started for the Raiders (3-0) and went to the seventh to pick 
up his first win. 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego 4-3, Cal Lutheran 2-5 -- Cal Lutheran rallied in the second game 
of a nonconference doubleheader at UC San Diego to earn a split as pitcher 
Kevin O'Neill picked up his first win. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran (2-1) had just one hit in the first game. Trailing, 2-0, in the 
second game, the Kingsmen scored four in the fourth and one in the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
Master's 2, Dominguez Hills 2 -- After 13 innings, darkness ended the 
nonconference game at Dominguez Hills. Mustang pitcher Jeff Cole give up just 
four hits in 8 2/3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
Master's (0-4-1) scored both of its runs in the seventh, when Jeff Peterson 
doubled home Peter Wilson and scored on a throwing error. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Only one Cal Lutheran player managed to win a set in the second round of an 
invitational tournament hosted by Cal State Bakersfield at Twin Lakes Racquet 
Club in Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
Marja Helsten of CLU won the second set of her No. 3 singles match against Dawn 
Blysma of UC Riverside, but lost the match, 6-0, 3-6, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
CS Northridge d. Chapman, 15-0, 15-6, 15-5 -- Raphael Tulino recorded 10 kills 
and Chris Faucher added eight for Northridge in the nonconference match at 
Chapman. 
</P>
