<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part 3; Page 19; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
140 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
HOME RUNS HELP CYPRESS GAIN TODAY'S FINAL IN OWN EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jason Friedman, Doug Yates and Mike Neal hit home runs to help the Cypress 
College baseball team defeat Golden West, 11-1, Saturday in the Cypress 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Friedman hit a three-run home run in the fourth, and Yates followed with a solo 
homer as Cypress took a 4-0 lead. Neal hit his homer in the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
Dennis Burbank, a sophomore transfer from Pepperdine, pitched eight innings, 
allowing a run and getting eight strikeouts for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress moved into the championship game Monday at 2 p.m. at Cypress. Citrus 
and El Camino play today at 10 a.m., and the winner plays at Golden West at 2 
p.m. for the right to play Cypress for the title. 
</P>
<P>
In men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 8, UC Santa Barbara JV 1 -- No. 1 singles player Carl Hinds swept 
UCSB's Mike Boice, a former No. 1 player from Saddleback, 6-3, 6-2, at UC Santa 
Barbara. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
